Pseudo-Code: Main process description

  1. Become aligned with the wall
  2. Follow wall while still being aligned with wall
  3. Check hall effect to see if we've passed tesseract
  4. On finding tesseract, use sweeping arm to hit into bucket
    -Drive set distance
    -Activate sweep arm
    -Wait for tesseract to settle
  5. Initiate spiralling out sequence from the wall, check IR sensor for bearing on beacon
  6. Go towards beacon, if heading is lost spin "in place" until we find it again
  7. Arrive at beacon, stop a set distance from it
  8. Pick up the beacon using the claw
    -Will simultaneously mechanically release cube
  9. Back up set distance
  10. Place beacon down onto cube

End Description
